article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. -- — Jahari Williamson's 15 points helped Niagara defeat LIU 60-52 on Sunday. Williamson went 5 of 10 from the field (3 for 6 from 3-point range) for the Purple Eagles (3-5). Olumide Adelodun added 12 points while shooting 4 of 5 from the field and 3 for 3 from the line while they also had six rebounds. Jhaylon Martinez shot 4 of 5 from the field and 3 for 3 from the line to finish with 11 points. Terell Strickland finished with 17 points, five assists and two steals for the Sharks (3-7). Malachi Davis added 15 points and two steals for LIU. Jalen Lee also had eight points. NEXT UP Niagara plays Friday against Siena at home, and LIU hosts York (NY) on Wednesday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
